[{"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T18:57:53+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Various models of iPhone 16 with a graphic background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/52vtvsLAoZdwZwYEDPCaqUbQUUw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72025718/247288_iPhone_Buying_Guides_2_CVirginia.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>New iPhones for the AI era.</em> | Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Whether you want a battery that lasts for days or the very best deal, we\u2019ve got some recommendations for an iPhone you\u2019ll love.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23618862/best-iphone-camera-battery-screen-guide\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1562508, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23618862/best-iphone-camera-battery-screen-guide", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best iPhones", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T18:19:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vehicle-to-everything communication\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CqR_faXieryudD2igKm7E7XXn-0=/67x0:616x366/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73739363/Fcyv3EnWQAEQFMm.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://twitter.com/Research_USDOT/status/1570823856507478025\" target=\"_blank\">Department of Transportation</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"qzfwu2\">The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) has voted to <a href=\"https://www.fcc.gov/document/fcc-adopts-c-v2x-auto-safety-spectrum-rules\">finalize new spectrum rules</a> that will push cellular vehicle-to-everything (C-V2X) communications technology forward. </p>\n<p id=\"c4sbQX\">C-V2X will use existing cellular networks to send messages from vehicle to vehicle, vehicle to infrastructure, vehicle to cyclists, or vehicle to pedestrians to warn of each other's presence for safety purposes. It could cross-alert for hazardous road conditions, includin", "id": 1562509, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/21/24302733/fcc-cv2x-cellular-vehicle-everything-spectrum-rules-final", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "FCC passes auto safety spectrum rules", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T17:04:15+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Rabbit R1.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BnBgsrpmsr4J7hxtccXnlEOskjY=/0x0:6000x4000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73739232/Rabbit_R1_Settings.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: David Pierce / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yss5kl\">Rabbit is <a href=\"https://www.rabbit.tech/newsroom/teach-mode-beta\">rolling out \u201cteach mode\u201d to its R1 devices,</a> allowing you to create an AI agent that can perform tasks for you. The feature works by \u201clearning\u201d a task you demonstrate, such as retrieving updates from a content creator you follow, or helping you draft a post on social media.</p>\n<p id=\"BSajYF\">You can <a href=\"https://www.rabbit.tech/teachmode\">access the feature</a> by logging into the Rabbithole, the web interface for managing an R1 device. From there, you\u2019ll create a \u201clesson\u201d by describing a task and then recording yourself performing it. Once you show the AI agent what you want it to do, ", "id": 1562154, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/21/24302600/rabbit-r1-ai-agent-teach-mode-tasks", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Rabbit now lets you teach the R1 to perform tasks for you", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T17:01:35+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Apple logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0fifiJ8blYmLA0hFF18rnCQAReE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73739224/STK071_APPLE_N.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MZh9Ps\">Apple is planning a major AI overhaul of Siri that will make the digital assistant more like OpenAI\u2019s ChatGPT and Google\u2019s Gemini Live, <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-21/apple-readies-more-conversational-llm-siri-in-bid-to-rival-openai-s-chatgpt\">according to a report from <em>Bloomberg</em>\u2019s Mark Gurman</a>. The assistant, reportedly called \u201cLLM Siri,\u201d will be powered by Apple\u2019s AI models and will let users have more conversational, natural-sounding interactions with Siri.</p>\n<p id=\"sZqhIW\">As part of Apple\u2019s plan to infuse its iPhones with AI, <em>Bloomberg</em> says the company will make Siri better at handling more advanc", "id": 1562155, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/21/24302685/apple-llm-siri-compete-chatgpt", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple is reportedly working on \u2018LLM Siri\u2019 to compete with ChatGPT", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T16:46:13+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the ChatGPT logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fP9PFIsRuAJwTY7_PYi35xk_xV4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73739181/STK155_OPEN_AI_CVirginia_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ORk7LO\">In a stunning misstep, OpenAI engineers accidentally erased critical evidence gathered by <em>The New York Times</em> and other major newspapers in their lawsuit over AI training data, according to a court filing Wednesday.</p>\n<p id=\"BZpxk3\">The newspapers\u2019 legal teams had spent over 150 hours searching through OpenAI\u2019s AI training data to find instances where their news articles were included, the filing claims. But it doesn\u2019t explain how this mistake occurred or what precisely the data included. While the filing says OpenAI admitted to the error and tried to recover the data, what it managed to salvage was incomplete and unreliable \u2014 so what was recove", "id": 1561702, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/21/24302606/openai-erases-evidence-in-training-data-lawsuit", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "OpenAI accidentally erases potential evidence in training data lawsuit", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T16:15:49+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing Donald Trump on a red and green background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xiKUQDHL_DYafQ3w87gnTnxw1ko=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73739114/VRG_Illo_STK175_L_Normand_DonaldTrump_Negative.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Laura Normand / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"2AVide\">The auto industry is sending an urgent message to President-elect Donald Trump: spare the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/4/20/23691597/ev-tax-credit-eligible-vehicles-battery-irs-china\">$7,500 electric vehicle tax credit</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"irmbqp\">In a November 14th letter to Trump and his transition team, the auto industry\u2019s main lobbying group urges the new administration to preserve incentives for EV buyers and manufacturers that were enacted under President Joe Biden, arguing these policies keep the US competitive globally while also creating \u201cgood jobs.\u201d </p>\n<p id=\"1HrkIj\">The Alliance for", "id": 1561703, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/21/24302592/trump-ev-tax-credit-auto-alliance-av-framework", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Automakers plead with Trump: don\u2019t kill the EV tax credit", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T16:05:54+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Android logo on a green and blue background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RGkv6gi-hj8JTfAJAGSXMDn_4LA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73739104/acastro_STK112_android_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5TwzIl\">Transferring your data from your old Android device<strong> </strong>to a new one will soon be less daunting,<strong> </strong>thanks to \u201cRestore Credentials,\u201d a new developer feature for Android<strong> </strong>which can <a href=\"https://android-developers.googleblog.com/2024/11/maintain-strong-user-relationships-with-restore-credentials.html\">keep you logged into your apps</a> when you make the switch. While some apps already did this, Google is making it easier for developers to include this experience by implementing a \u201crestore key\u201d that automatically transfers to the new phone and logs you back into the app.</p>\n<p id=\"cH08s", "id": 1561704, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/21/24302562/android-restore-credentials-transfer-restore-key", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "It will soon be easier than ever for Android apps to stay signed in on a new phone", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "author": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-21T15:08:49+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/R6DUbXPR94uvcYe6jmO2vkKqbqA=/115x0:1357x828/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73738973/Screen_Shot_2024_04_26_at_1.29.30_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Eken</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wepoed\">The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) <a href=\"https://docs.fcc.gov/public/attachments/DOC-407668A1.pdf\">is proposing more than $700,000 in fines</a> against Eken, a Hong Kong-based video doorbell manufacturer whose products were 